<br>
The other night, I made a careless pull while soloing in SD. I wound up with two Bloodtribe shamen. Their spells were highly effective against me once they landed malisement. I got rooted and root wouldn't break. (The mobs were attacking my pet, but would periodically stop to throw a few spells in my direction.)<br>
<br>
I did manage to gate to safety, but the casting mobs can be much more effective now than they were before.<br>
<br>
If I'm careful about what I'm doing, and keep the mob's attention directed to my pet, the resist changes have made things easier for me. <br>
<br>
Pet spells are doing landing much more effectively than before. Soloing with Vocerate Earth, I have twice gone linkdead in the middle of a fight. The pet root spell is lasting long enough for me to still be alive when I log back in.<br>
<br>
EDIT: Followup question. It used to be that when a pet got charmed, it would &lt;poof&gt;, correct?  Now that the pets are actually being charmed, is it possible that if the mage goes LD, the pet will 'stick around' until the mage 'poofs'?<br>
